The Vice President held a meeting to discuss the implementation of the Economic Recovery Act. He emphasized the importance of helping those affected by the economy, creating jobs, and building a sustainable economy. Two examples of Recovery Act funds were announced: a one-time payment of $250 for seniors receiving Social Security, and a $3.2 billion investment in state and local energy efficiency programs. The Vice President expressed confidence in the progress made so far and discussed upcoming plans for infrastructure, renewable energy, and education. He also introduced the new CEO in charge of the operation and requested feedback from the Cabinet members on their agency's progress and potential changes.